    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-09-07T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-09-07T11:00:00-05:00" n="540"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d540">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/9–754: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Sweden</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_LODGEHCJ1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-09-07T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 7, 1954—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>160. In reply to representation made in conformity with Department’s instructions
                        (<gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 167, September 3)<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d540fn1">Not printed.</note> Foreign Minister pointed out to me that
                    Sweden had always taken position that Communist China should be admitted to
                        <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> and that government could not now reverse
                    its position even on basis of a procedural question. He mentioned that at
                    Reykjavik meeting Denmark and Norway had shifted their positions towards
                    favoring admission of Communist China.</p>
                <p>British Ambassador informs me he has seen minutes of Reykjavik decision and that
                    it is not so completely negative from our viewpoint as
                        <persName>Unden</persName> and news reports indicate. Expect to get from him
                    and transmit its substance.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LODGEHCJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cabot</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
